OL,3,CWoman feared test error would rob
OL,4,Cchildren of their mum
OL,6,FTwo women who developed cancer after
OL,7,Ftheir smear tests were misread have
OL,8,Fspoken out about their experiences and
OL,9,Fthe devastating effect it had on their
OL,10,Flives. Both women have asked to remain
OL,11,Fanonymous.
OL,13,FIt comes as three reports into the
OL,14,Fcervical smear review in the Southern
OL,15,FTrust were released.
OL,17,FCaroline - who was diagnosed with
OL,18,Fcancer in 2022 - has told UTV that she
OL,19,Fthought she "wasn't going to survive"
OL,20,Fand her four children would "be left
OL,21,Fwithout a mum".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/9
