OL,6,FThe mother-of-four wants a public
OL,7,Finquiry to get to the truth.
OL,9,F'Emma' was diagnosed with cancer in
OL,10,F2021 - she was told in 2024 her smear
OL,11,Ftest had also been misread.
OL,13,F"I can say, diagnosis changes you. It
OL,14,Fchanges your whole outlook on life.
OL,16,F"You'd be thinking about the future
OL,17,Fand it is there in the background
OL,18,Fconstantly.
OL,20,F"You do think, 'What if?'
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/9
