OL,6,F"It's just that it was avoidable. The
OL,7,Fonly person that ever apologised to me
OL,8,Fwas the consultant in the meeting.
OL,10,F"He said, 'I'm sorry, that should have
OL,11,Fbeen caught. It wasn't .... I'm not
OL,12,Fafraid to stand up and say that'.
OL,14,F"But again, that was not reflected in
OL,15,Fthe minutes of the meeting. I think
OL,16,Fwe've all been treated just as a
OL,17,Fnumber on a page.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/9
